The '''Filanovsky Oil Field''' is an [[oil field]] located in the Caspian Sea. It was discovered in 1994 and developed by [[Lukoil]]. The oil field is owned and operated by [[Lukoil]]. The total [[proven reserves]] of the Filanovsky oil field are around 1.27 billion barrels (170×10<sup>6</sup> tonnes), and production is centered on {{convert|160000|oilbbl/d|m3/d}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oilru.com/or/43/886/|title=Lukoils caspian gambit|date=2010|publisher=Oil of Russia|accessdate=2013-05-25}}</ref>
