'''''Nay Eretra Sämunawi Gazét'a''''' ('Eritrean Weekly News') was a [[Tigrinya language|Tigrinya-language]] newspaper published in [[Eritrea]]. The newspaper, which was founded in 1942 (during the [[Italian_Eritrea#British_occupation_and_the_end_of_the_colony|British Mandate]] period), was issued by the [[British Information Service]]. The newspaper was closed down in 1953, when the [[Ethiopia]]n imperial government banned all Eritrean publications.<ref>Simpson, Andrew. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=I7qsTVO4IK4C Language and National Identity in Africa]''. Oxford [u.a.]: Oxford Univ. Press, 2008. p. 277</ref>

