[[File:Swin_Golf.jpg|thumb|A ball and a swingolf club}]]
[[File:Flight_Island.JPG|thumb|A Swingolf game in Iceland]]
'''Swingolf''' is a family-oriented variation of [[golf]] that has is played with a single golf club and softer, bigger balls, giving access to inexperienced and young players.{{Citation needed|date=June 2016}}

This sport is usually played casually, similar to [[mini-golf]], but also has a league.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.leswin.com/|title=French League of Swingolf|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=14 June 2016}}</ref>

The golf courses are usually less well-kept than normal courses.{{Citation needed|date=June 2016}} They are often planted with grass that fits local climate, reducing watering and maintenance and thus reducing cost.{{Citation needed|date=June 2016}}

This sport is mainly popular in Europe, especially in France, Germany, Switzerland, and Austria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.leswin.com/terrains/|title=Où jouer? – Fédération Sportive de Swin-Golf|website=www.leswin.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>

== Differences with Golf ==
* The fees to play Swingolf is usually much lower, ranging from 8 to €15 for an adult per game.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.swingolfneuchatel.ch/prix.php|title=Swin Golf Pierre-À-Bot|website=www.swingolfneuchatel.ch|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.golfdeneuchatel.ch/en/tarifs|title=Tarifs - Golf & Country Club de Neuchâtel|last=Utilisateur|first=Super|website=www.golfdeneuchatel.ch|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>
* It can be played by kids starting at 8 year old and family without prior experience after a 10min introduction.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.laligue14.org/ufolep/IMG/pdf/Regles_de_jeu_swin_golf.pdf|title=Swingolf Rules|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>
* The balls, bigger than golf and made of soft polymeric foam reduces the risk of injuries or damage in case of impact.
* The game is played with a single club that is usually lent, reducing the hassle to carry several clubs.
* The course is much smaller than usual golf course and is ranging from 30'000 to 90'000m2.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mguiheneuc.free.fr/topic3/index.html|title=Swin concept|website=mguiheneuc.free.fr|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>
* The course is usually less kept than traditional golf, reducing maintenance cost and water usage.
* Due to the less kept course, ball trajectory might be less predictable.
* The range is shorter due to the bigger and softer ball to about 150–200 meters for a strike.Swin golf is easier than golf for kids.

== History ==
Swingolf was created in 1982 by Laurent de Vilmorin and mainly expanded in western Europe in countries where golf is expensive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.golfdeneuchatel.ch/en/tarifs|title=Tarifs - Golf & Country Club de Neuchâtel|last=Utilisateur|first=Super|website=www.golfdeneuchatel.ch|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>

